03Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022 face=\u0022Calibri\u0022 size=\u00223\u0022\u003ECourtesy of LordPrometheus / Spanner:\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0in 0in 8pt;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cfont face=\u0022Calibri\u0022\u003EAdded - AT4\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-23T18:23:52Z\u0022 title=\u002202/23/2016 06:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 23, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by V8jester\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheSpaceManiac","CreatedById":152329,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-23T19:06:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI remeber this was mentioned briefly on this thread a while ago now, but is there a mod that could allow Kerbals to move in groups? (Perhaps the pilot Ai could be \u0027tricked\u0027 into doing this)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-23T21:08:21Z\u0022 title=\u002202/23/2016 09:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 23, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by TheSpaceManiac\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Esecond suggestion removed, issue resolved\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"V8jester","CreatedById":136093,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-23T19:36:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222426165\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119991\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456254414\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152329\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSpaceManiac\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, TheSpaceManiac said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI remeber this was mentioned briefly on this thread a while ago now, but is there a mod that could allow Kerbals to move in groups? (Perhaps the pilot Ai could be \u0027tricked\u0027 into doing this)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso a small suggestion would be to cause Kerbals spawning into seats on launch with TakeCommand to automatically be set to be on the same team as the \u0027parent\u0027 vessel to prevent accidental teamkills (happened to me once...)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a mod to make kerbals move either independently (fallowing a path) or on command (go to a point)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/84476-025-eva-follower-v103-05-nov-2014/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=1894174\u0022\u003EEVA Fallowers - Patched for 1.0.5\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot\u00A0sure how I\u0027d\u00A0handle team spawning\u00A0like that. But I\u0027ll keep that in mind.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Space Scumbag","CreatedById":70411,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-23T20:02:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally, my Troopers will love the Blaster! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I have some ideas for the nect updates. You will get a pm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BF2_Pilot","CreatedById":155577,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-25T14:41:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMay I use your Kis CFG\uFF1F\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to make some\u00A0PLA\u00A0weapons for me\u00A0like QJY-88 and QBZ-95\u3002\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"V8jester","CreatedById":136093,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-25T15:01:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222429086\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119991\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456411266\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155577\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BF2_Pilot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, BF2_Pilot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMay I use your Kis CFG\uFF1F\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to make some\u00A0PLA\u00A0weapons for me\u00A0like QJY-88 and QBZ-95\u3002\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFPS wouldn\u0027t even exist had it not been for several people sharing what they had.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-26T22:59:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222429086\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119991\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456411266\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155577\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BF2_Pilot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 25/02/2016 at 2:41 PM, BF2_Pilot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMay I use your Kis CFG\uFF1F\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to make some\u00A0PLA\u00A0weapons for me\u00A0like QJY-88 and QBZ-95\u3002\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne thing to be aware of though, longer weapons tend to look a bit odd\u00A0 and those mentioned a very long and spindly so some scaling will be needed, drop me a line if you get stuck though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I been asked about doing some laser weapon type stuff for this mod and I\u0027m still not convinced that they will be awesome, but i\u0027m willing to give it a try, so the pic below is likely to be the first laser firing weapon in the FPS armory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/DOrLFlE.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022DOrLFlE.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn other news, still doing stuff for future releases, and working on current annoyances, leaning towards dropping the existing javelin launcher as its just to fiddly to use, I have run up and tested to death and passed on to Jester\u00A0 a much simpler version that doesn\u0027t force you to try and align the damn missile in a tube, kis it seems just doesn\u0027t care about collisions at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"V8jester","CreatedById":136093,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-26T23:14:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222431465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119991\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456527547\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250907\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpannerMonkey(smce)\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, SpannerMonkey(smce) said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne thing to be aware of though, longer weapons tend to look a bit odd\u00A0 and those mentioned a very long and spindly so some scaling will be needed, drop me a line if you get stuck though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I been asked about doing some laser weapon type stuff for this mod and I\u0027m still not convinced that they will be awesome, but i\u0027m willing to give it a try, so the pic below is likely to be the first laser firing weapon in the FPS armory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn other news, still doing stuff for future releases, and working on current annoyances, leaning towards dropping the existing javelin launcher as its just to fiddly to use, I have run up and tested to death and passed on to Jester\u00A0 a much simpler version that doesn\u0027t force you to try and align the damn missile in a tube, kis it seems just doesn\u0027t care about collisions at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like the idea of a simplified Javelin using the Hellfire. Gives you the proper cold launch and flight path. Downside is having to use the right click menu to fire. But I think the Pro\u0027s far outweigh the Con\u0027s\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso I added your Pic to the WIP section\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shooty boomy","CreatedById":159457,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T16:29:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhy not add a ironsights feature by adding a iva on the gun that moves with the gun\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"V8jester","CreatedById":136093,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-28T21:38:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222433612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119991\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456676940\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159457\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022shooty boomy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, shooty boomy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhy not add a ironsights feature by adding a iva on the gun that moves with the gun\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forums.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe issue with adding either and \u0022IVA\u0022 or a hull cam module. Is that either way the sight would remain stationary while the gun moves. Basically in the current state of things it\u0027s just not possible. Yes it can be done it just won\u0027t fallow the gun like a first person shooter style game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}